        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 5:27PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 526 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 8 miles east of Whitehall to near Three Forks to
Belgrade. Movement was north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Belgrade, Three Forks, Manhattan, Toston, Bozeman Hot Springs,
Missouri Headwaters State Park, Cardwell, Logan, Radersburg, Lewis
And Clark Caverns State Park, Maudlow, Four Corners, Amsterdam,
Trident, Church Hill, Willow Creek, Menard, and Madison Buffalo Jump
State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Isolated
lightning strikes will be possible with these showers.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
southwestern Montana.</instruction>
